%h2 Class04 Answer:
%h2 On Linux install Oracle Java.

%p
  To install Java, I need to download jdk-8u162-linux-x64.tar.gz from Oracle:

%p
  %a(href='http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html' target='x')
    http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html
  

%p
  After the download, I install Java with the syntax listed below:

.syntax
  %pre
    %code.bash
      cd ~
      tar xf ~/Downloads/jdk-8u162-linux-x64.tar.gz
      ln -s jdk1.8.0_162 jdk
      echo 'export JAVA_HOME=${HOME}/jdk'       >> ~/.bashrc
      echo 'export PATH=${JAVA_HOME}/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
      bash
      java -version
%p
